Overview.Summary: The 2019 Abkhazian presidential election took place on September 8 (3). The voter turnout was at 39.14% after 15 hours of voting (2). Incumbent President Raul Khajimba won the runoff with 47.38% of the vote (4). Khajimba was also invited by Russian President Vladimir Putin to attend the celebration of the 75th anniversary of WWII (1). The election was recognized as valid by the Central Election Commission (3,7). Khajimba's candidacy was supported by an initiative group (6). Other countries, such as Uruguay, also held presidential elections in 2019 (5). The International Olympic Committee implemented changes to future Olympic Games elections (10). There were also other significant elections in 2019, such as the European Parliament elections (9), Tunisia's presidential election (14), and Austria's national election (16). The death of former Tunisian President Beji Caid Essebsi also impacted the election landscape (17). Elections in Papua New Guinea also took place in 2019 (18). The Presidential Election Petition Tribunal in Nigeria ruled in favor of President Muhammadu Buhari (15,19). In Canada, the election results for the Northwest Territories were announced (12). The riding of Northwest Territories encompasses the entire northern Canadian territory (12). The Democratic Party held a presidential primary debate on November 20, 2019 (11). In Manitoba, Canada, the incumbent premier called for an early election (20).
